by orlangur at 2017-03-08T17:46:31Z

@SpacePossum thanks for pointing to this PR, I tried to search for "yoda" and "cond" with no luck and thought `YodaConditionFixer` was renamed to something less predictable.

Why Yoda-style is default one in AutomateEverything era? Most of experienced programmers have got some professional deformation and read `null === $something` better than `$something === null`?

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by SpacePossum at 2017-03-08T18:32:21Z

The rationale behind the defaults in this project (and this PR) are based on:
- current CS in the project
- expected most used values

I added the options to prevent discussion about what is best and why. With the options everyone can use the fixer as wanted. So lets see what options are missing, what bugs are left in this PR or where other improvements can be made here.

